## 2-Dimensional Array in Programming

A 2-dimensional array is a type of array that has two dimensions or axes. It's often used to represent tables, matrices, or grids of data. Here's an example of how you can create and manipulate a 2D array in different programming languages:

### Java Example
```java
int[][] myArray = new int[3][4];

// Initialize the array with values
myArray[0][0] = 1;
myArray[0][1] = 2;
myArray[0][2] = 3;
myArray[0][3] = 4;

myArray[1][0] = 5;
myArray[1][1] = 6;
myArray[1][2] = 7;
myArray[1][3] = 8;

myArray[2][0] = 9;
myArray[2][1] = 10;
myArray[2][2] = 11;
myArray[2][3] = 12;

// Print the array
for (int i = 0; i < myArray.length; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < myArray[i].length; j++) {
        System.out.print(myArray[i][j] + " ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

